P.M. BRIEFING; 
L.A.-DUSSELDORF FLIGHTS DUE JUNE 13 
Lufthansa German Airlines announced today that it will begin service between 
Los Angeles and Dusseldorf, West Germany, on June 13. The non-stop services 
will operate twice weekly and continue on to Munich -- offering Lufthansa's 
first Los Angeles-Munich flights. 
An excursion fare of $699 will be offered between June 13 and July 13 as an 
introduction to the service, Lufthansa said. 
